who meet these criteria,

03:33.213 --> 03:36.308
but given what you
witnessed in Africa,

03:36.466 --> 03:39.436
you are exactly what I need.

04:01.116 --> 04:03.210
- Business or pleasure?
- What?

04:03.368 --> 04:06.338
Seventeen hours in airplane
seats not suited for children.

04:06.997 --> 04:09.420
Two hours trying to hail a cab.

04:09.583 --> 04:11.881
Another hour searching
through city streets

04:12.043 --> 04:15.343
with teens dressed
like circus clowns.

04:15.714 --> 04:17.057
And did I mention,

04:17.214 --> 04:19.889
I haven't been off the African
Continent in over a decade?

04:20.051 --> 04:22.725
So I am asking,
which one do we conquer first?

04:22.888 --> 04:25.016
- Business or pleasure?
- Let's find the address,

04:25.182 --> 04:28.903
then you can partake in whatever
it is you feel like partaking.

04:32.939 --> 04:34.737
ABRAHAM: This is it.

04:34.900 --> 04:36.618
[DOOR Buzzlis]

04:41.907 --> 04:45.207
We are looking for the former
residence of Dr. Robert Oz.

04:45.952 --> 04:47.704
Jackson?

04:57.088 --> 04:59.090
[CLASSIC ROCK PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

05:03.845 --> 05:05.597
MITCH: Thank you.

05:08.433 --> 05:11.903
And now we border
treacherously on stalking.

05:12.062 --> 05:14.281
I don't know whether to be
freaked out or flattered.

05:14.439 --> 05:16.066
Be grateful.

05:17.484 --> 05:18.531
What's that?

05:18.693 --> 05:21.367
The paper offered to fly us to New
Orleans to meet Senator Vaughn.

05:21.530 --> 05:23.730
He's head of the Environment
and Public Works Committee.

05:24.741 --> 05:26.243
A little premature,
don't you think?

05:26.409 --> 05:27.929
We have evidence
against Reiden Global.

05:27.994 --> 05:30.622
We don't have anything
close to solid evidence.

05:30.789 --> 05:32.917
Are you kidding me?

05:33.083 --> 05:36.007
We know those lions were
communicating over large distances.

05:36.169 --> 05:37.796
That's not evidence.
It's a theory.

05:38.505 --> 05:40.098
Yes, we have a mutation

05:40.257 --> 05:43.431
that seems to be producing
a hive-like mind in lions.

05:43.593 --> 05:45.766
Same kind that exists in bees,

05:45.929 --> 05:47.522
some kind of superorganism.

05:47.681 --> 05:49.433
But that's more crazy
than anything else.

05:49.599 --> 05:52.478
And it's a hell of a long way off
from pinning the blame on Reiden.

05:52.644 --> 05:54.692
Look, Senator Vaughn is
from my home district.

05:54.855 --> 05:56.653
He's a good man. He will listen.

05:56.815 --> 06:00.695
Our theory is at least enough to
get him to launch an investigation.

06:00.861 --> 06:05.367
Look, I have classes, I have students.
I have laundry.

06:05.532 --> 06:07.705
I would think that if
there's even a possibility

06:07.868 --> 06:10.621
that Reiden Global is turning
lions into superorganisms,

06:10.787 --> 06:13.256
that that would be a priority for
you, but it's fine.

06:13.415 --> 06:16.339
I'll just, um, take my findings
to a guy I know at Caltech.

06:16.501 --> 06:19.050
Oh, now they're your findings?

06:19.588 --> 06:24.094
This is the kind of stuff that
leads to tenure and chairmanships.

06:24.259 --> 06:27.354
Appealing to what you
perceive to be my outsized ego

06:27.512 --> 06:29.355
lacks subtlety.

06:29.514 --> 06:32.609
And Louisiana is lovely
this time of year.

06:38.732 --> 06:43.238
I recognize you from a handful
of photos your father kept.

06:44.029 --> 06:45.656
I apologize, Minako.

06:45.822 --> 06:48.496
I had no idea that my
father had got remarried.

06:48.658 --> 06:49.910
Ah.

06:50.410 --> 06:52.458
Please sit.

06:53.705 --> 06:56.504
We met at Harvard six years ago.

06:56.666 --> 06:57.918
[SPEAKS IN JAPAN ESE]

06:58.084 --> 07:00.428
I was writing my thesis on

07:00.587 --> 07:04.012
trophics interaction
and plankton ecology,

07:04.174 --> 07:08.725
and I became fascinated with
Robert's work on animal evolution.

07:08.887 --> 07:12.187
After he was fired
from the university,

07:12.349 --> 07:16.274
he sunk into a deep depression.

07:16.436 --> 07:18.814
I convinced him to
continue his work

07:18.980 --> 07:23.451
and offered to use my
family's money to sustain us.

07:23.985 --> 07:27.455
He was, at that time,
quite penniless.

07:27.614 --> 07:31.118
- So you were with him during...?
- His breakdown?

07:31.660 --> 07:33.207
Yes.

07:33.954 --> 07:36.503
Love is difficult...

07:37.290 --> 07:40.339
When you stick with someone
during the hard times.

07:40.502 --> 07:44.723
But, of course,
that is when they need you the most.

07:46.508 --> 07:48.510
If you have come now,

07:48.677 --> 07:51.351
two years after
your father's death,

07:51.513 --> 07:54.187
it must be because
you need something.

07:57.477 --> 08:01.277
A pride of male
lions in Africa...

08:01.439 --> 08:05.694
Their..
Their behavior was, uh...

08:05.860 --> 08:07.362
Troubling.

08:07.529 --> 08:09.827
I believe that my father
may have additional research

08:09.990 --> 08:13.119
that can shed some further
light on the lions',

08:13.284 --> 08:15.457
um, changing behavior.

08:18.415 --> 08:19.792
So it has begun.

08:23.628 --> 08:28.384
The awakening of the
animals' cognitive acuity.

08:30.260 --> 08:32.479
I would love to give you the
rest of your father's work,

08:32.636 --> 08:35.640
but it is not here.

08:36.474 --> 08:40.104
It remains where he conducted
his final experiments.

08:40.270 --> 08:41.863
And where is that?

08:45.275 --> 08:47.323
MINAKO: Your father
became paranoid.

08:48.361 --> 08:50.739
He began hiding his findings.

08:50.905 --> 08:53.784
Coding everything, even from me.

08:53.950 --> 08:57.500
I finally convinced him that
somebody other than himself

08:57.662 --> 09:00.836
needed to be in on his genius.

09:00.999 --> 09:03.001
- What are those?
- Rad meters.

09:03.168 --> 09:05.421
You need to wear
these at all times.

09:05.587 --> 09:08.340
They let us know when we've
taken in too much radiation.

09:09.215 --> 09:12.059
Why should we be worried
about radiation exposure?

09:12.594 --> 09:17.065
Your father selected an island 30
kilometers outside of Fukushima.

09:17.891 --> 09:19.234
Fukushima?

09:19.392 --> 09:22.145
As in nuclear reactors,

09:22.312 --> 09:25.486
radiation leaks
and deadly fallout?

09:25.648 --> 09:29.278
He called it his "Ghost
of Christmas Future."

09:30.070 --> 09:33.745
Coming to this island
worked for your father.

09:33.907 --> 09:37.537
The last time we spoke,
he was so thrilled.

09:37.702 --> 09:39.545
He said he finally understood.

09:40.830 --> 09:44.380
- Understood what?
- I suspect

09:44.542 --> 09:47.466
why the animal behavior was changing.
I don't know.

09:47.629 --> 09:50.178
He did not want to
say on the phone.

09:50.340 --> 09:53.719
But before I could
make the trip out here.

09:53.885 --> 09:55.262
