30:09.266 --> 30:11.519
And your fervent
desire for confirmation

30:11.685 --> 30:13.938
as to whether or not

30:14.104 --> 30:19.235
lions can now communicate
over long distances.

30:20.444 --> 30:23.994
Mystery Man in a Very Nice
Suit Who Knows Things.

30:24.156 --> 30:25.749
Yeah.

30:28.618 --> 30:31.918
- All right, I'm in.
- Very good.

30:32.080 --> 30:34.503
On one condition.

30:46.720 --> 30:48.563
BLANCHARD: I'm surprised
you agreed to see me.

30:50.557 --> 30:52.059
EVAN LEE: Seems it's God's will.

30:52.809 --> 30:56.188
Or some might say
a veiled attempt

30:56.355 --> 31:01.862
to stave off any kind of unforeseen
unpleasantness in the hereafter.

31:02.527 --> 31:05.997
But I don't answer to them,
Miss Blanchard, only to you.

31:06.156 --> 31:07.954
It's Missus.

31:10.410 --> 31:13.163
You've always maintained
your innocence.

31:14.122 --> 31:16.841
But I need the
truth, Mr. Hartley.

31:18.543 --> 31:20.921
Did you kill my husband?

31:25.592 --> 31:28.562
I wasn't always like this.

31:28.970 --> 31:30.938
Lusting.

31:31.473 --> 31:33.225
Craving.

31:35.018 --> 31:37.771
We played God.

31:37.938 --> 31:41.283
And we paid a horrible price.

31:41.441 --> 31:44.240
I was out there
looking for the cure.

31:44.403 --> 31:46.576
Out there in the woods.

31:47.531 --> 31:50.910
That night,
seeing your husband and his friends

31:51.660 --> 31:54.288
on that hunting trip,

31:55.580 --> 31:57.708
it triggered something.

31:58.959 --> 32:03.305
Watching men celebrate murder.

32:04.339 --> 32:06.341
They made it easy.

32:06.508 --> 32:09.011
Easy to kill.

32:10.595 --> 32:13.189
Your husband was the first.

32:14.015 --> 32:15.983
He was a little
slower than the rest.

32:16.143 --> 32:18.862
I took him down fast.

32:19.271 --> 32:22.400
You should know he didn't
suffer, Miss Blanchard.

32:22.566 --> 32:23.988
My knife is fast.

32:24.151 --> 32:26.028
Missus.

32:26.653 --> 32:28.533
And before I got caught,
I was out there looking

32:28.697 --> 32:30.699
for another hunting party.

32:30.866 --> 32:32.994
Because it had become...

32:34.953 --> 32:37.752
It is now

32:37.914 --> 32:39.791
my nature.

32:39.958 --> 32:43.087
I know you got questions
about what I did.

32:43.253 --> 32:47.429
But all the answers are right
here, Miss Blanchard.

32:47.591 --> 32:48.968
Damn it, it's missus.

32:49.509 --> 32:52.228
- Mrs. Blanchard.
- Is it, though?

32:53.805 --> 32:55.432
Is it still?

32:55.599 --> 32:59.775
You see,
I thought I removed the missus

32:59.936 --> 33:01.734
when I removed Daniel's heart.

33:01.897 --> 33:04.821
Guard! I want to leave now!

33:04.983 --> 33:08.783
Guard! Open this door right now!

33:09.237 --> 33:13.583
RICHARD: Day 47: The deHant pupil
has been present for 16 days.

33:14.367 --> 33:17.712
I have failed in isolating
and reversing the mutations.

33:17.871 --> 33:20.294
The horses are becoming
increasingly aggressive.

33:20.457 --> 33:23.301
This is impossible.
Everything is in code.

33:23.460 --> 33:24.586
[SIGHS]

33:26.087 --> 33:28.431
A little help here, Jackson?

33:30.425 --> 33:32.519
The eyes are the
window to the soul.

33:32.677 --> 33:34.520
How does that help
to decode this stuff?

33:34.679 --> 33:39.185
Like you said before,
perception stains reality.

33:39.351 --> 33:40.819
What if...

33:42.103 --> 33:44.947
The defiant pupil is a signifier

33:45.106 --> 33:49.407
that the way the animals see
the world is now changing?

33:49.569 --> 33:52.789
It's affecting how they
interpret what they see.

33:54.282 --> 33:58.378
What used to be a
friend is now an enemy.

33:58.537 --> 34:01.040
And because of this,

34:01.456 --> 34:03.424
